16/11/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Authorities launched the second stage of a voluntary arms collection operation Saturday (15 November), two weeks after phase one began.
Amnesty is being offered to those who turn in illegal weapons and ammunition by the 15 December deadline.
In other news, President Boris Trajkovski met on Friday with visiting German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder, who pledged his country's support for Macedonia's ambition to join the EU and NATO.
They also discussed Kosovo, agreeing that the "standards before status" principle is the best approach to determining the province's future.
(MIA - 15/11/03;
MIA - 14/11/03)
